01:32:49,663 --> 01:32:52,863
He say me make trip
go Norway any day.

1323
01:32:53,530 --> 01:32:55,929
But I too busy.

1324
01:32:55,930 --> 01:32:56,961
Always too busy.

1325
01:32:56,962 --> 01:33:00,929
Now Jesus give me special gift
go Norway.

1326
01:33:03,197 --> 01:33:06,796
Thank you, Mr. Dusan.
Thank you, Mr. Konrad.

1327
01:33:08,730 --> 01:33:11,862
Yes. I go Norway, too.

1328
01:33:11,863 --> 01:33:13,728
So happy!

1329
01:33:13,729 --> 01:33:16,061
Thank you special time.

1330
01:35:16,523 --> 01:35:17,953
Paul, look.

1331
01:35:17,956 --> 01:35:21,155
This Jorgen Asbjornsen
and he wife.

1332
01:35:22,823 --> 01:35:25,889
Oh, my God.
Jorgen Asbjornsen?

1333
01:35:27,090 --> 01:35:28,488
Hello.

1334
01:35:28,489 --> 01:35:31,586
- It's just such an honor.
- Hello, hello.

1335
01:35:31,587 --> 01:35:32,854
See, Paul?

1336
01:35:33,389 --> 01:35:34,953
Jesus smile for me.

1337
01:35:34,954 --> 01:35:38,088
I say Paul I want visit Norway
only for meet you.

1338
01:35:38,622 --> 01:35:39,819
It's true.

1339
01:35:39,822 --> 01:35:42,154
- I'm Anne-Helene.
- Hello.

1340
01:35:42,155 --> 01:35:44,154
Please sit. Join us.

1341
01:35:44,155 --> 01:35:45,487
Thank you.

1342
01:35:45,488 --> 01:35:47,252
We're watching
the world go by.

1343
01:35:47,255 --> 01:35:49,554
Sounds great.

1344
01:35:49,555 --> 01:35:51,621
You have no idea
how terribly grief-stricken

1345
01:35:51,622 --> 01:35:54,386
we were by Miss Tran's case.

1346
01:35:54,387 --> 01:35:58,188
Jorgen has lost so much sleep
over all the abuses.

1347
01:36:08,520 --> 01:36:10,287
It's humbling, huh?

1348
01:36:11,354 --> 01:36:14,685
Nature is such
a patient sculptor.

1349
01:36:14,686 --> 01:36:16,685
Grinding a tiny bit

1350
01:36:16,686 --> 01:36:20,118
each day, slowly, slowly,
for thousands of years,

1351
01:36:20,119 --> 01:36:25,154
to make such a supremely
beautiful thing.

1352
01:36:27,420 --> 01:36:28,953
What a waste.

1353
01:36:30,886 --> 01:36:34,087
What a dreadful waste.

1354
01:36:43,786 --> 01:36:45,585
You'll have to excuse Jorgen.

1355
01:36:45,587 --> 01:36:49,117
These past few days
has been especially hard.

1356
01:36:49,118 --> 01:36:52,283
Such a big decision to make,
and so quickly.

1357
01:36:52,284 --> 01:36:55,184
Normally, when we visit the
colony, we like to spend

1358
01:36:55,185 --> 01:36:58,884
a few days in Henningsvar,
but then the news came.

1359
01:36:59,685 --> 01:37:00,983
And...

1360
01:37:00,984 --> 01:37:04,783
Yeah, well, here we are,
suddenly imposing on you.

1361
01:37:04,784 --> 01:37:06,917
We scarcely
had the time to pack.

1362
01:37:07,819 --> 01:37:10,550
I'm sorry, wait, what news?

1363
01:37:10,551 --> 01:37:13,149
Why, the methane release
in Antarctica.

1364
01:37:13,150 --> 01:37:15,317
You must know
about the methane.

1365
01:37:16,350 --> 01:37:17,615
Yeah.

1366
01:37:17,618 --> 01:37:19,416
That's not new, is it?
I mean...

1367
01:37:20,650 --> 01:37:22,317
New or old,

1368
01:37:23,118 --> 01:37:24,717
it's the end.

1369
01:37:25,583 --> 01:37:28,384
It's the end of everything.

1370
01:37:30,382 --> 01:37:34,814
The world has already seen
five major extinctions,

1371
01:37:34,815 --> 01:37:37,015
and now there will be another.

1372
01:37:37,016 --> 01:37:40,814
I didn't want to believe it,
none of us did,

1373
01:37:40,815 --> 01:37:44,980
but there we were in Helsinki,
big and small:

1374
01:37:44,983 --> 01:37:47,912
Climatologists,
bacteriologists,

1375
01:37:47,914 --> 01:37:51,715
demographers, physicists,
immunologists.

1376
01:37:51,716 --> 01:37:55,779
Twenty-six Nobel Prize winners
among us.

1377
01:37:55,782 --> 01:37:58,515
We built all the models,
did all the math

1378
01:37:58,516 --> 01:38:02,113
and our conclusion
was consistent.

1379
01:38:02,114 --> 01:38:06,645
Homo sapiens will soon vanish
from the Earth.

1380
01:38:06,648 --> 01:38:09,780
It is now an actuarial
certainty.

1381
01:38:10,646 --> 01:38:13,380
No matter
how the end will come,

1382
01:38:13,381 --> 01:38:15,680
environmental disaster,

1383
01:38:15,681 --> 01:38:18,712
pandemic disease,
unbreathable air,

1384
01:38:18,713 --> 01:38:20,180
impotable water,

1385
01:38:20,181 --> 01:38:22,845
not enough food,
nuclear winter,

1386
01:38:22,846 --> 01:38:25,913
some combination of them all,

1387
01:38:26,747 --> 01:38:28,880
relatively soon the Earth will

1388
01:38:28,881 --> 01:38:31,947
indeed purge itself
of human life

1389
01:38:32,980 --> 01:38:35,980
and God knows
how many other species.

1390
01:38:37,447 --> 01:38:38,813
Do you really mean extinction?

1391
01:38:38,814 --> 01:38:40,511
What about downsizing?

1392
01:38:40,512 --> 01:38:42,644
Yeah, yeah,
too little too late.

1393
01:38:42,645 --> 01:38:45,676
Only 3% of the world
has miniaturized.

1394
01:38:45,679 --> 01:38:47,846
There simply
isn't enough time.

1395
01:38:51,613 --> 01:38:55,644
Not a very successful species,
these Homo sapiens,

1396
01:38:55,645 --> 01:38:58,711
even with such
great intelligence.

1397
01:38:58,712 --> 01:39:01,778
Barely 200,000 years.

1398
01:39:01,779 --> 01:39:04,411
Alligator has survived
200 million years

1399
01:39:04,412 --> 01:39:06,978
with a brain
the size of a walnut.

1400
01:39:11,512 --> 01:39:12,743
People have
been predicting

1401
01:39:12,744 --> 01:39:15,444
the end of the world
for thousands of years.

1402
01:39:16,445 --> 01:39:18,445
Now it's really happening.

1403
01:39:20,779 --> 01:39:23,310
I guess somebody
had to be right someday.

1404
01:39:24,677 --> 01:39:26,212
So sad.

1405
01:39:27,578 --> 01:39:29,043
Very sad.

1406
01:39:43,043 --> 01:39:46,444
Okay, I go sleep now.
Good night, Paul.

1407
01:39:47,310 --> 01:39:49,243
Good night, Ngoc Lan.

1408
01:39:53,643 --> 01:39:56,109
- You okay?
- I fine.

1409
01:39:56,110 --> 01:39:58,875
You know, maybe I should
take a look at your leg.

1410
01:39:58,877 --> 01:40:01,074
Okay. Yes, you look.

1411
01:40:05,676 --> 01:40:07,007
Ah, yep.

1412
01:40:07,342 --> 01:40:09,073
Wow.

1413
01:40:09,076 --> 01:40:12,076
That peg is really
making the skin chafe.

1414
01:40:12,609 --> 01:40:14,240
Okay.

1415
01:40:21,608 --> 01:40:22,641
You know,

1416
01:40:23,641 --> 01:40:26,041
if somebody had told me
10 years ago

1417
01:40:26,042 --> 01:40:29,439
that one day I'd be
five inches tall and divorced

1418
01:40:29,440 --> 01:40:32,671
helping a famous Vietnamese
dissident get a new foot

1419
01:40:32,673 --> 01:40:35,104
while cruising up a fjord
in Norway

1420
01:40:35,106 --> 01:40:36,573
discussing the end
of the world

1421
01:40:36,574 --> 01:40:38,108
with Jorgen Asbjornsen,

1422
01:40:39,141 --> 01:40:41,274
I'd have said he was crazy.

1423
01:41:16,605 --> 01:41:18,136
I'm sorry.

1424
01:41:18,139 --> 01:41:20,569
I'm sorry, I thought...

1425
01:41:20,570 --> 01:41:22,171
Jesus, I'm such an idiot.

1426
01:41:22,605 --> 01:41:23,605
No.

1427
01:41:25,471 --> 01:41:28,005
Please. I want.

1428
01:42:05,070 --> 01:42:06,537
Good morning.

1429
01:42:08,802 --> 01:42:10,270
Good morning.

1430
01:42:13,802 --> 01:42:15,301
What's that sound?

1431
01:42:15,802 --> 01:42:17,269
A greeting.

1432
01:43:50,631 --> 01:43:54,529
Wow! That's it.
That's the original colony!

1433
01:43:54,530 --> 01:43:57,395
What, and there's no net?
No walls?

1434
01:43:57,398 --> 01:43:58,697
No, we've been lucky.

1435
01:43:58,698 --> 01:44:02,261
We are too close to the sea
for the mosquitoes.

1436
01:44:02,264 --> 01:44:04,962
And over the years
we realized that the birds,

1437
01:44:04,963 --> 01:44:07,130
they prefer the lemmings.

1438
01:44:07,131 --> 01:44:09,863
But, yes, this is
where we started

1439
01:44:09,864 --> 01:44:11,396
many years ago.

1440
01:44:46,462 --> 01:44:49,060
George,
good to see you.

1441
01:44:49,061 --> 01:44:50,993
Good to see you.
Welcome, welcome.

1442
01:44:50,994 --> 01:44:52,261
No, no...

1443
01:44:52,262 --> 01:44:53,462
Jorgen!

1444
01:44:54,128 --> 01:44:55,725
Anne-Helene!

1445
01:44:55,728 --> 01:45:00,462
Oh, thank God you're here!
Why didn't anyone tell me?

1446
01:45:00,795 --> 01:45:01,960
Oh!

1447
01:45:01,962 --> 01:45:04,627
I love you so much!

1448
01:45:05,427 --> 01:45:07,828
I love you both so much.

1449
01:45:08,728 --> 01:45:10,091
Ever since the decision,

1450
01:45:10,094 --> 01:45:12,127
I didn't feel right
without you here.

1451
01:45:12,128 --> 01:45:14,060
And you know how I am
when I worry.

1452
01:45:14,061 --> 01:45:16,027
I can't eat, I can't sleep.

1453
01:45:16,029 --> 01:45:18,292
Ask anyone here,
they tell you.

1454
01:45:18,293 --> 01:45:20,559
Sorry to interrupt, Jorgen,

1455
01:45:20,560 --> 01:45:22,960
