Immediately.

1456
01:45:22,962 --> 01:45:24,692
Yes. Excuse us, Solveig.

1457
01:45:24,694 --> 01:45:25,591
Of course, darling.

1458
01:45:25,592 --> 01:45:27,926
You've got important
things to do.

1459
01:45:29,226 --> 01:45:32,189
Oh! Dusan, Dusan, Dusan!

1460
01:45:32,192 --> 01:45:35,458
Bless you for
coming so quickly.

1461
01:45:37,793 --> 01:45:39,326
Solveig, my darling.

1462
01:45:39,328 --> 01:45:42,189
I'm always happy
to help in difficult times,

1463
01:45:42,192 --> 01:45:43,457
in easy times, in happy times.

1464
01:45:43,458 --> 01:45:45,692
It's always a pleasure
to come and visit you

1465
01:45:45,694 --> 01:45:47,457
and your lovely village.

1466
01:45:47,458 --> 01:45:49,923
- It is lovely, isn't it?
- Oh.

1467
01:45:49,926 --> 01:45:53,990
I can't bear to think
I won't see it again.

1468
01:45:53,993 --> 01:45:55,657
You know, I'm the one
who made

1469
01:45:55,658 --> 01:45:58,490
this colony possible
in the first place.

1470
01:45:58,493 --> 01:46:01,823
I've been coming
since I was just a baby.

1471
01:46:01,824 --> 01:46:03,958
I remember one time...

1472
01:46:04,690 --> 01:46:07,591
Wait. I know you.

1473
01:46:07,592 --> 01:46:10,390
You were in
my dream last night!

1474
01:46:10,391 --> 01:46:13,122
You were a horse, or a pony.

1475
01:46:13,125 --> 01:46:15,055
Something very strong!

1476
01:46:15,057 --> 01:46:16,590
And I mounted you

1477
01:46:16,591 --> 01:46:20,988
and rode you through
a dangerous forest.

1478
01:46:20,989 --> 01:46:23,855
- Okay.
- And here you are,

1479
01:46:23,858 --> 01:46:26,256
right before we leave.

1480
01:46:26,257 --> 01:46:28,654
Another miracle!

1481
01:46:28,655 --> 01:46:31,788
You are coming with us,
aren't you?

1482
01:46:31,791 --> 01:46:32,989
Where are you going?

1483
01:46:34,922 --> 01:46:36,720
In there.

1484
01:46:36,722 --> 01:46:38,422
Would you like to see?

1485
01:46:50,355 --> 01:46:51,689
Where this go?

1486
01:46:52,256 --> 01:46:54,256
To the vault!

1487
01:46:54,989 --> 01:46:56,854
- The vault?
- Oh, yes.

1488
01:46:56,855 --> 01:46:58,020
We've been working on it

1489
01:46:58,021 --> 01:47:00,520
almost since
the very beginning.

1490
01:47:00,521 --> 01:47:03,188
When Jorgen made
his big discovery,

1491
01:47:03,189 --> 01:47:06,252
I said, look, Jorgen,
you're a genius

1492
01:47:06,255 --> 01:47:08,488
and downsizing
is a genius idea,

1493
01:47:08,489 --> 01:47:10,587
no one is questioning that,

1494
01:47:10,588 --> 01:47:14,353
but what if people
don't accept it?

1495
01:47:14,354 --> 01:47:17,587
What if it doesn't
come out on time?

1496
01:47:17,588 --> 01:47:20,153
Anyway, this is what
they came up with.

1497
01:47:20,154 --> 01:47:22,787
On my suggestion.

1498
01:47:22,788 --> 01:47:24,353
Torvald, be a sweetheart

1499
01:47:24,354 --> 01:47:26,787
and give our friends
a little tour.

